Redescription:
Habitus and coloring as in 

. Pterodimorphous; brachypterous specimens (

) with reduced humeral angles and abdominal tergite VII without palisade fringe. Head subquadrate. Penultimate antennal segment quadrate. Mesotibia slender. Body surface with distinct, dense, setose punctation, without microreticulation. Pubescence of body surface short, decumbent, without conspicuous macrosetae. Body orange-brown with light, yellow-brown appendages (

) to reddish medium brown with orange-brown posterior fifth of elytra, often somewhat lighter brown shoulders or basis of elytra, light brown tip of abdomen, light brown maxillary palpi and legs (

); antennae gradually lighter from medium brown scapus to light brown segment 11. Total body length 
2.4 – 2.9 mm
; forebody length 
1.4 – 1.6 mm
.

Male:Abdominal sternite VII with unmodified posterior margin. Abdominal sternite VIII with posterior margin evenly concave in posterior fifth (

).Aedeagus (

, 

) about 
0.7 mm
long; apical lobes with convex ventral margins (

) and, in ventral and dorsal view, round apicolateral margins (

: arrow 
II
, 

); dorsal lobe strongly curved ventrad, strongly projecting from apical lobes ventrally, with round, lobiform end (

: arrow I); flagellum short, inconspicuous; lateral lobes evenly convex, not much projecting (

), with group of numerous, apicad and ventromediad pointing setae [setae broken off in 

, 

, but insertion points visible (for setation compare with aedeagus of 

S. batukaruensis

, 

)]; transverse ridge of small, semicircular median foramen narrow, curved proximad (

).

